Author: inovica
Title: Ask YC: Has anyone used Amazon Mechanical Turk?
Content:
Hi there

We're considering trying out the Amazon Mechanical Turk for data input to one of our systems where we feel the quality of data is very important. We have a crawler and are wanting to categorize the information. We have looked at algorithms for this (with good results) but are wanting to check these results and also add to them. Amazon sure gave this a crazy name, but I'm curious to find out if anyone has actually used it and what are your findings

Author: cmars232
Content:
I still haven't worked out the protocols for matching encoded locations -- hopefully it is possible. I fear you're right, I may not be able to get beyond a simple challenge-response type of comparison without disclosing some information.

Cool thing is, since I got interested in solving this problem, I've learned how R-Trees work! :)
